EDM-2001: Performance improvements for steady state scenario

This change addresses 2 main problems during testing of large population
during steady state scenario:
- The periodic update status operation done by the device agent takes a
  lot of resources - mainly database.
- The periodic get rendered device takes a lot of resources - also
  database.

This PR tries to reduce the load by performming the following:
- Reduce the frequency of the messages.
- Remove periodic access to the databse on behalf of a single device.

The following changes were made:
- Add new healthcheck endpoint.  Let the agent send this request every 2
  minutes.
- Make the agent send update status only if the status changed from the
  last time it was sent.
- Make the server check if rendered version changed in redis. If it has
  not, wait for such notification for 2 minutes before returning to the
  client.
- Let the server accumulate healthchecdk requests, and update last_seen
  field for multiple devices instead of single device.
